name: Main Library - All gender restroom - Room 442

name: Main Library - All gender restroom - Room 401B
directions: This restroom is on the fourth floor of the Main Library and is most closely located near elevator E-5. Take a left when you leave the elevator, then a right, and another right. The restroom is on the left towards the end of the hall.

name: Main Library - All gender restroom - Room 46
directions: This restroom is on the basement level and is accessible from within the Library by taking the E-1 elevator and from the outside via the ramp on the West side of the building (by the parking lot) or the "Room 66" stairs outside the Wright Street (North) entrance to the Library.

name: The Breakfast Club London Bridge
directions: Both bathrooms are next to each other at the back of the restaurant in a small hallway.
comment: *in terms of accessibility there is a smallish step up to the restaurant then the rest is flat and open (though there are many tables there should be space, I’ve seen wheelchairs users here). There are three toilets, one disabled which requires a staff key or a radar and two stalls in a unisex bathroom, though these stalls are quite tight and there is one small sink. As this is a restaurant being able to use the bathroom without being a customer is up to staff discretion but I have seen staff allow non customers to use the restroom multiple times. I haven’t been for a while I believe they do have a changing table but I can’t remember so left it as no to be safe.
